            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1519.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the shepherd's pie is cooking, chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then wash to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into batons</p><p>Wipe the pan clean and return it to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and <strong>courgette batons</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until soft and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1519.-step-7-x200.jpg",
